## Brainstorm decisions (2026-05-06)

1. **Route shape:** `/live` as separate route with own layout under `(auth)` route group
2. **Pass balance:** Server Component layout fetches entitlements; `router.refresh()` on post-purchase; no SWR/Zustand
3. **Landing page:** Distinct `/` — value prop landing page (Claude Design variant C); auth users redirect to `/dashboard`
4. **Auth pattern:** Server-fetched session + thin `<UserProvider>` client context; Zustand auth slice dropped
5. **Token sequencing:** Tokens first — Wave 1 before any component work

**Cross-cutting principle:** Prefer Server Components. Zustand for client-only interactive state only (kit edits, pick log, UI toggles).

**Revised wave order for plan 010a:**
1. Design system baseline (globals.css tokens + shadcn bridge, fonts, Tailwind config)
2. Shell + landing (AppShell, UserProvider, middleware, `/` landing, auth route group)
3. Pre-draft workspace (KitSwitcher, kits slice, auth pages, PreDraftWorkspace)
4. Session API + state (draftSession slice, draft-sessions client, entitlements client)
5. Live draft screen (LiveDraftScreen, manual pick drawer, reconnect banner)

